title.rendered: Bob Dylan Drops “Like a Rolling Stone” Music Video

content.rendered:
Reading Time: < 1 minute

Bob Dylan has stolen the music video headlines from Kanye West.

On the same day that rapper released his Kim Kardashian-filled video for "Bound 2," the iconic rocker came out with the official video for "Like a Rolling Stone."

Yes, nearly half a century after that track’s release.

The special video was designed by a company called Interlude and it allows the viewer to channel surf, as one is able to flip around and watch various individuals – including a few celebrities – lip-synching to the iconic tune he first released in 1965.

Not following along? Press Play on the Interactive footage now:
